<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,925,614,640]" box="[189,925,614,640]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,431,614,640]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Emended diagnosis</emphasis>
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." box="[624,917,614,640]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,661,757]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
As for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerlach" authorityYear="1963" box="[278,373,662,688]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,373,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), but amphids almost never completely surrounded by body annulations (seldom more than half of amphids surrounded by body annulations), amphids are entirely surrounded by annuli in some rare cases; tail conico-cylindrical to filiform. Precloacal supplements usually present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,348,796,822]" box="[189,348,796,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,348,796,822]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,348,796,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Valid species</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,843,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="(Castro et al., 2006)" authorityName="Leduc &amp; Verschelde" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Castro et al." baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[189,578,843,869]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="elongata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,324,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. elongata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Castro F. J. V. &amp; Bezerra T. N. C. &amp; Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[342,570,843,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref10284" refString="Castro F. J. V., Bezerra T. N. C., Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2006. Spirinia elongata, sp. nov. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from Pina Basin, Pernambuco, Brazil. Zootaxa 1121: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2006">
Castro 
<emphasis box="[430,492,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,721,843,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Castro et al., 2006" authorityName="Castro" authorityYear="2006" box="[867,1314,843,870]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[867,1074,843,870]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia elongata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Castro F. J. V. &amp; Bezerra T. N. C. &amp; Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[1084,1314,843,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref10284" refString="Castro F. J. V., Bezerra T. N. C., Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2006. Spirinia elongata, sp. nov. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from Pina Basin, Pernambuco, Brazil. Zootaxa 1121: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2006">
Castro 
<emphasis box="[1171,1233,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Main diagnostic characters: “...one very small subventral tooth and two small dorsal teeth.” The drawings show amphids completely surrounded by body annulations, but the authors describe a conico-cylindrical tail with annuli which are more evident in the tail region compared to those along the rest of the body; thus, we transfer this species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[563,674,985,1010]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[563,674,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Castro F. J. V. &amp; Bezerra T. N. C. &amp; Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[689,904,984,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref10284" refString="Castro F. J. V., Bezerra T. N. C., Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2006. Spirinia elongata, sp. nov. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from Pina Basin, Pernambuco, Brazil. Zootaxa 1121: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2006">
Castro 
<emphasis box="[775,834,984,1010]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 3c, 4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,1049,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Vitiello, 1971" authorityName="Vitiello" authorityYear="1971" box="[189,497,1049,1076]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="flagellata">
<emphasis box="[189,327,1049,1076]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. flagellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vitiello P." box="[333,497,1049,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="647 - 690" refId="ref11590" refString="Vitiello P. 1971. Nematodes libres marins des vases profondes du Golfe du Lion III. Monhysterida, Araeolaimida, Desmodorida. Tethys 2: 647 - 690." type="journal article" year="1971">Vitiello, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Main diagnostic characters: “Amphid situated anterior to cuticle striations or partially surrounded by them”; very long and slender, almost filiform tail (
<bibRefCitation author="Vitiello P." box="[1059,1219,1084,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="647 - 690" refId="ref11590" refString="Vitiello P. 1971. Nematodes libres marins des vases profondes du Golfe du Lion III. Monhysterida, Araeolaimida, Desmodorida. Tethys 2: 647 - 690." type="journal article" year="1971">Vitiello 1971</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 29).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1150,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Wieser &amp; Hopper, 1967" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[189,615,1150,1176]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis box="[189,310,1150,1176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. hamata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B." box="[320,615,1150,1176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="239 - 343" refId="ref11687" refString="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B. 1967. Marine nematodes of the east coast of North America. I. Florida. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 135: 239 - 343." type="journal article" year="1967">Wieser &amp; Hopper, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Drawing shows amphids only partially located within the body annuli; long and slender, almost filiform tail (
<bibRefCitation author="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B." box="[720,1000,1185,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="239 - 343" refId="ref11687" refString="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B. 1967. Marine nematodes of the east coast of North America. I. Florida. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 135: 239 - 343." type="journal article" year="1967">Wieser &amp; Hopper 1967</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 18).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1250,1418]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="(Silva et al., 2009)" authorityName="Leduc &amp; Verschelde" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Silva et al." baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[189,511,1250,1277]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="lara" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,270,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. lara</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silva M. C. &amp; Castro F. J. V. &amp; Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[289,502,1250,1277]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref11270" refString="Silva M. C., Castro F. J. V., Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2009. Spirinia lara sp. n. and Spirinia sophia sp. n. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from the Brazilian continental margin (Campos Basin, Rio de Janeiro). Zootaxa 2081: 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[362,431,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.,</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[522,655,1250,1276]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva et al., 2009" authorityName="Silva" authorityYear="2009" box="[802,1182,1250,1278]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="lara">
<emphasis box="[802,956,1250,1278]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia lara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Silva M. C. &amp; Castro F. J. V. &amp; Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[967,1182,1250,1277]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref11270" refString="Silva M. C., Castro F. J. V., Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2009. Spirinia lara sp. n. and Spirinia sophia sp. n. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from the Brazilian continental margin (Campos Basin, Rio de Janeiro). Zootaxa 2081: 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[1038,1100,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Main diagnostic characters: “Buccal cavity with one dorsal tooth and two minute ventrosublateral teeth” and “Cuticle with transverse striae..., less obvious in head region than in tail.” Drawing shows amphid with annulations to mid-level of amphid only, and tail is described as conico-cylindrical. This species is therefore transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[219,330,1393,1418]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[219,330,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silva M. C. &amp; Castro F. J. V. &amp; Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[345,544,1391,1418]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref11270" refString="Silva M. C., Castro F. J. V., Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2009. Spirinia lara sp. n. and Spirinia sophia sp. n. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from the Brazilian continental margin (Campos Basin, Rio de Janeiro). Zootaxa 2081: 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[415,473,1391,1418]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2–3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1457,1553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989" authorityName="Vincx &amp; Gourbault" authorityYear="1989" box="[189,679,1457,1483]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="megamphida">
<emphasis box="[189,369,1457,1483]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. megamphida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." box="[376,679,1457,1483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Drawing shows substantial portion of the amphids is located on the non-annulated lip region; conico-cylindrical tail with more prominent annuli (
<bibRefCitation author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault 1989</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,1593,1654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Coles, 1987" authorityName="Coles" authorityYear="1987" box="[189,434,1593,1619]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mokii">
<emphasis box="[189,283,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. mokii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Coles J. W." box="[290,434,1593,1619]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="79 - 101" refId="ref10455" refString="Coles J. W. 1987. Observations on the marine nematode genus Spirinia Gerlach, 1963 (Desmodoridae: Spiriniinae) with descriptions of two new species. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 53: 79 - 101." type="journal article" year="1987">Coles, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Main diagnostic character: ‘‘...cuticle appears smooth…’’, hence amphids are not surrounded by annuli; long and slender filiform tail (
<bibRefCitation author="Coles J. W." box="[805,944,1628,1654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="79 - 101" refId="ref10455" refString="Coles J. W. 1987. Observations on the marine nematode genus Spirinia Gerlach, 1963 (Desmodoridae: Spiriniinae) with descriptions of two new species. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 53: 79 - 101." type="journal article" year="1987">Coles 1987</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1693,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989" authorityName="Vincx &amp; Gourbault" authorityYear="1989" box="[189,644,1693,1720]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="papillata">
<emphasis box="[189,326,1693,1720]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. papillata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." box="[335,644,1693,1719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Drawing shows anterior half of amphids on non-annulated lip region and posterior half located within the annulated head region; long, conico-cylindrical tail (
<bibRefCitation author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault 1989</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1829,1961]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authority="(Cobb, 1914)" authorityName="Leduc &amp; Verschelde" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Cobb" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[189,554,1829,1855]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="septentrionalis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,391,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. septentrionalis</emphasis>
(Cobb, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[561,690,1829,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonyms: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cobb, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Cobb" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[840,1279,1829,1856]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis box="[840,1116,1829,1856]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia septentrionalis</emphasis>
(Cobb, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cobb, 1914" authorityName="Cobb" authorityYear="1914" baseAuthorityName="Cobb" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Peranemea" family="Astasiidae" genus="Spira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Natomonadida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spira septentrionalis</emphasis>
Cobb, 1914
</taxonomicName>
). Main diagnostic characters: ‘‘From the anus the tail tapers for two-thirds of its length, then becomes cylindroid to the swollen terminus…’’ Drawings by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wieser W." box="[1125,1288,1899,1925]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref11656" refString="Wieser W. 1954. Free-living nematodes II. Chromadoroidea. Lunds Universitets Arsskrift, N. F. Avd. 2 50 (16): 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1954">Wieser (1954</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 126) clearly show the amphids in the head region with only their posterior half within the body annulations,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,266,327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
leaving the anterior half on the non-annulated head region. The tail is conico-cylindrical. Thus, this species is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[591,702,302,327]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[591,702,302,327]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,366,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authority="(Timm, 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Timm" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[189,575,366,393]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="striaticaudata">
<emphasis box="[189,389,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. striaticaudata</emphasis>
(Timm, 1962)
</taxonomicName>
. Tail long (11–17 abd) and slender with distinct annuli; thus it is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[353,464,403,428]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[353,464,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Synonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Timm, 1962" authorityName="Timm" authorityYear="1962" box="[614,1027,401,428]" class="Chromadorea" family="Linhomoeidae" genus="Spirina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monhysterida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="striaticaudata">
<emphasis box="[614,873,401,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Spirina striaticaudata</emphasis>
Timm, 1962
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,420,466,493]" box="[189,420,466,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,420,466,493]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,420,466,493]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Species inquirenda</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,513,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName box="[189,433,513,540]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="sabulicola">
<emphasis box="[189,433,513,540]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria sabulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Filipjev, 1918/1921) comb. nov. (synonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Filipjev, 1918" authorityName="Filipjev" authorityYear="1918" box="[992,1390,513,540]" class="Chromadorea" family="Linhomoeidae" genus="Spirina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monhysterida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="sabulicola">
<emphasis box="[992,1212,513,540]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Spirina sabulicola</emphasis>
Filipjev, 1918
</taxonomicName>
/ 1921). This species was described with a ‘long tail (length 4 × width)’ and hence should be transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[339,450,585,610]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[339,450,585,610]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, as the species was described based on only one female, it is regarded as a 
<emphasis box="[241,461,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">species inquirenda</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
